1
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,532
(HAPPY HOLIDAY PLAYING)

2
00:00:33,617 --> 00:00:36,368
Happy holiday

3
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:39,622
Happy holiday

4
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,020
(PLAYING HARMONICA)

5
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:50,025
Merry Christmas, bud.

6
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,151
Thank you.
Merry Christmas to you.

7
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:52,903
Okay. Hi, Chief.

8
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:56,156
(BELL RINGING)

9
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:37,823
(JIM WHISTLING TUNE)

10
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,122
Come in.

11
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,124
Hello, honey.

12
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:49,627
(KISSING)

13
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,921
Well, this is
our last night in show business.

14
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,380
Some feeling, huh?

15
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:55,299
Some feeling.

16
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:57,009
I got the ring
and the license.

17
00:02:57,093 --> 00:02:59,511
Honey, we're ready.
Oh.

18
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:02,097
Say, there's
a hook left over at the top here.

19
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:03,307
Should that be?

20
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:05,601
Never mind,
I'll take care of it.

21
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:08,520
Jim?
Huh?

22
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,399
(SIGHS)

23
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:15,778
Well, I think that
tie's terrible.

24
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:18,364
(CHUCKLES) Well, who cares?
Tomorrow I'm a farmer.

25
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:19,531
You'd better
go change it.

26
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:21,700
Listen, honey,
when you're flipping those twinkle toes

27
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:23,452
who's gonna be
looking at my tie?

28
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:25,287
You only have
five minutes. Hurry.

29
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:27,247
Okay, I'm on my way.

30
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:42,680
What'd he say?

31
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,348
I didn't tell him.

32
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:46,100
Why not?
We love each other.

33
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,893
You wanna
continue dancing.

34
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,813
I know,
but he gets a look.

35
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:52,648
Oh, he's always had
that look.

36
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:54,441
It doesn't mean
anything emotionally.

37
00:03:54,526 --> 00:03:56,235
It has something to do
with his liver.

38
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,028
Simply tell him
you had made a mistake.

39
00:03:58,113 --> 00:04:00,280
You don't wanna
give up your career and live on a farm.

40
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:02,783
But he's already
bought the farm.

41
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:05,536
And the license,
and the ring.

42
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:07,997
Oh, I can't tell him.

43
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:11,250
All right, I will.
Right after our number.

44
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:13,377
Listen, darling,
don't weaken.

45
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:14,837
Think of our life
together.

46
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,214
Think of diamonds,
of sables,

47
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:18,882
of your own
little penthouse.

48
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:20,676
Is that a promise?

49
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:23,012
Well, just think
about them for the time being.

50
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,096
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

51
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,180
MAN: Ready, Miss Dixon.

52
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,598
Well, thank you.

53
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,434
Say, this thing
didn't come out even.

54
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:31,478
Oh, I'll fix it.
We have to hurry.

55
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:34,481
I love you.

56
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:35,607
I love you...

57
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,235
...and Jim.

58
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:42,364
I love Jim, too.
But after all, I mean, let's not be too chummy.

59
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:43,490
(LAUGHS)

60
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:46,285
(BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYING)

61
00:04:57,672 --> 00:05:00,049
(I'LL CAPTURE YOUR HEART
PLAYING)

62
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:10,184
(SINGING) Here she comes
down the street

63
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,269
My, oh my,
ain't she sweet?

64
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:15,272
Why, here comes
my hot toddy

65
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:17,900
Over my dead body

66
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:24,448
I'll capture
her heart singing

67
00:05:24,532 --> 00:05:29,328
Just wait until
she gets a load of my dancing

68
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:36,335
Just wait till
I start singing

69
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:40,756
I'll take her strolling
down the road with my dancing

70
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,509
I can't go wrong,
a tender song

71
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,761
And she'll discover
my charms

72
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:48,388
Some fancy taps
and she'll collapse

73
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:51,100
And fall right
into my arms

74
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:57,940
I'll capture
her heart singing

75
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,109
Oh, no,
you haven't a chance

76
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:02,569
When I go
into my dance

77
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:14,706
I'll take you
through life singing

78
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:16,583
(SCATTING)

79
00:06:26,261 --> 00:06:30,097
I'll make you
my wife dancing

80
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:40,274
If you could dance
instead of sing

81
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:42,651
I'd learn to
love you somehow

82
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,987
If you could sing
instead of dance

83
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,823
I'd take you home
with me now

84
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:50,033
(SCATTING)

85
00:06:55,039 --> 00:06:56,623
(WHISTLING)

86
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,298
The way you sing
don't mean a thing

87
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,758
You'd better stick
to your dance

88
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,303
And as for you,
your dance won't do

89
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,139
You'll have to
sing for romance

90
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,849
I'll capture her heart...

91
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,059
I'll capture her heart...

92
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,853
Singing
Dancing

93
00:07:20,023 --> 00:07:21,607
(SCATTING)

94
00:07:24,903 --> 00:07:26,486
(BOTH SCATTING)

95
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:43,837
(CONTINUES SCATTING)

96
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,813
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

97
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:06,902
Not much of
a Christmas present for you, is it?

98
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,863
I mean, both of us
walking out on you.

99
00:08:09,948 --> 00:08:12,449
Don't worry
about me, kid. I'll do all right.

100
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:13,909
(CHUCKLING)
What a chum.

101
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:16,578
Can't you see what
we're walking out on? The grind.

102
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:19,414
365 days a year.

103
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,250
When's the last time
you had as day off?

104
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,960
I don't know.
Maybe last year?

105
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:24,586
Do you ever hear
of Thanksgiving

106
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:27,005
or Labor Day
or the Fourth of July?

107
00:08:27,131 --> 00:08:29,132
Vaguely.
You know what they are, don't you?

108
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:30,676
They're holidays.

109
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,761
Days of rest.
There's lots of 'em.

110
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:34,179
They mark 'em in red
on the calendar

111
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:35,389
so you can't miss 'em.

112
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:38,100
What happens in
show business when a holiday comes along?

113
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:40,477
You give
an extra performance.

114
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:41,728
Not for me, brother.

115
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:44,314
Lila and I are
going up to that farm in Connecticut

116
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:47,109
and we're gonna live
by the calendar.

117
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,528
Say, Jim?
Mmm?

118
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:51,655
There's something
you should know.

119
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:54,408
Oh, I know, Ted.
I feel the same way about you.

120
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:57,286
You know, we've had
our ups and our downs

121
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,996
and we fought a little
over the women

122
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,247
we swiped from
each other, but...

123
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:02,791
I know, but...
Sorry, Jimmy boy, but that's life.

124
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:04,668
Ted, if I'm not
the best manager in the business

125
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:06,795
I'll eat a garage
mechanic's shirt.

126
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,505
Fifteen weeks
at the Park Club,

127
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:10,173
sight unseen,
for you and Lila.

128
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:14,344
$200 a week more
than you were getting with the farmer thrown in.

129
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,763
What's the matter?

130
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,516
I haven't told him.

131
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,310
You haven't told him?
You haven't told him?

132
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:23,895
Haven't told me what?
What... What's this? What's the news?

133
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,315
Well, don't be upset,
Jim, dear.

134
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,942
It isn't that
I don't love you. I do.

135
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:30,193
I love everybody,

136
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:33,697
but when Ted
explained how much he loved me and...

137
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:37,326
All at once,
we both realized that we belong together.

138
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:39,494
The two of us,
dedicating our lives

139
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:41,580
to making people happy
with our feet.

140
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:43,165
The two of you, huh?

141
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:46,335
Dedicating your lives
to making people happy with your feet.

142
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,919
That's sweet.

143
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:51,298
Well, I guess that
kick I just got was a good start, huh?

144
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,592
Sorry, Jimmy boy,
but that's life.

145
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,260
Yeah, it's best that
you found out now, Jim.

146
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:57,012
You wouldn't wanna
make Lila unhappy.

147
00:09:57,096 --> 00:10:00,140
Oh, no. No, I...
I wouldn't want to make Lila unhappy.

148
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:03,393
Not now, now that
I really know her.

149
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,103
(WHISTLES)

150
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:08,148
What a narrow
squeak that was.

151
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:09,191
What do you mean
by that?

152
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:11,526
Oh, nothing.
Nothing, honey.

153
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,986
I'm just happy
that you're happy.

154
00:10:13,071 --> 00:10:16,656
That little speech
sounds like the crack of a confederate money.

155
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:20,202
Well, kids,
I'm still gonna rejoin the human race.

156
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:23,413
I hope you get
a lot of work, holidays included,

157
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:26,708
dance yourselves
into beautiful nervous breakdowns.

158
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,545
You ever want to look me up,
you know where to find me,

159
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:34,966
Midville, Connecticut,
under a large shady tree,

160
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,760
just being lazy.

161
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:43,058
(SINGING) Lazy
I want to be lazy

162
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:48,188
I long to be out
in the sun

163
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:51,733
With no work
to be done

164
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:54,861
Under that awning

165
00:10:54,946 --> 00:10:58,698
They call the sky

166
00:10:58,783 --> 00:11:01,535
Stretching and yawning

167
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:06,373
And let the world
go drifting by

168
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,500
I want to peep

169
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:10,335
Through the deep

170
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:13,130
Tangled wildwood

171
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:17,217
Counting sheep
till I sleep

172
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:20,011
Like a child would

173
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:24,850
With a great
big valise full

174
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:27,894
Of books to read
where it's peaceful

175
00:11:27,979 --> 00:11:31,606
While I'm killing time

176
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:35,402
Being lazy

177
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,500
(ALARM RINGING)

178
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,262
(GLASS SHATTERS)

179
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:28,872
So Lazy Acres
was a snare and a delusion, huh?

180
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:32,000
Oh, brother,
there's the hardest work in the world.

181
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:34,336
Maybe you'd be happier
back in town, Jim.

182
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:36,379
Of course, if you get that
agricultural urge again,

183
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,006
you can always
raise a geranium.

184
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,425
Oh, no.
Wait till you hear.

185
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:42,385
I think I've dreamed up
the greatest idea I ever had.

186
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,678
And you've had some pips.

187
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:44,971
Oh, but this can't miss.

188
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:48,266
I'm turning
the farm into an inn, but what an inn.

189
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:50,727
Here, read up, brother.

190
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,605
"Holiday Inn,
Midville Connecticut."

191
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:57,275
(TED READING)

192
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,864
Open holidays only?
Mmm-hmm.

193
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:04,115
Say, how many
of those are there?

194
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,034
There's about 15.

195
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,787
That gives me
350 days a year to kick around in.

196
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:10,247
(LAUGHING) He would
think of that.

197
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:13,166
Did you get your
discharge papers from that sanitarium?

198
00:13:13,251 --> 00:13:15,919
Oh, don't you worry,
this is gonna work.

199
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:18,338
I'm having auditions
out at the farm every day.

200
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:19,548
Say, if you run
into any talent

201
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,757
that's willing to work
for a share of the table,

202
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:21,925
will you send them out?

203
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:23,552
Sure, soon as I get back.

204
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,136
I'm flying down to
Miami Beach tonight

205
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,556
to set an engagement
for Ted and Lila.

206
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,765
Lila.

207
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:30,267
You forgot to
order the flowers.

208
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:32,477
Now, don't get excited,
there's a flower shop out at the airport.

209
00:13:32,562 --> 00:13:35,188
I guarantee to have orchids
in her dressing room before her first number.

210
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,565
Oh, boy, you better.

211
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,609
As I remember,
this kid even expects presents on Father's Day.

212
00:13:39,694 --> 00:13:40,819
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

213
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:44,114
Well, good luck, Jim.
So long, Ted. Have a nice trip.

214
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,449
I mean, yeah,
thanks, I will.

215
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,911
That reminds me,
I forgot to give him a little

216
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:51,746
Christmas remembrance
I brought along.

217
00:13:51,831 --> 00:13:53,790
Got one here
for each of you.

218
00:13:55,084 --> 00:13:57,002
Say, this is swell.

219
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:58,920
What is it?

220
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,547
It's homemade
peach preserves.

221
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,049
I put them up myself,
just before I went into the sanitarium.

222
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:07,637
Boy, do I go for those.
Why, they're great on...

223
00:14:07,722 --> 00:14:08,930
Or even plain.

224
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:11,099
They're
non-fattening, too.

225
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,810
Well, it's a long trip
back to the farm, I think I'll get along.

226
00:14:13,894 --> 00:14:15,312
Will you say hello
to Lila for me?

227
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,730
But you gotta wait
and catch the act.

228
00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:19,858
We got some new routines
and then after the show... (BURSTS)

229
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:30,410
I don't think they like
this nightclub air.

230
00:14:31,037 --> 00:14:32,329
(BURSTS)

231
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:40,754
Wait. Wait. You better
wait for Lila's.

232
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:41,838
(BURSTS)

233
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:50,096
I think Danny's
was the loudest.

234
00:14:50,181 --> 00:14:51,723
Well, different tone.

235
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,519
Dawn patrol, huh?

236
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,152
Hello! Am I too late?

237
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,904
You would have been
in another minute.

238
00:15:09,784 --> 00:15:11,451
Danny Reed.

239
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:15,997
Listen, I have to
wait on that man.

240
00:15:16,082 --> 00:15:18,083
But...
I'll work five nights for you. Anything.

241
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,543
Just leave me alone
and don't butt in.

242
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:25,340
What would you like?

243
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,133
Orchids,
the finest you've got.

244
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:28,176
Corsage?

245
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,844
No. No. A dozen.

246
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,555
Loose, looking like
they don't care.

247
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:33,682
All right.

248
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,726
There,
"Lila, love, Ted."

249
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:38,645
Have them delivered
to Miss Lila Dixon

250
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,897
at the Club Pierre
before 11:00 tonight.

251
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:43,775
Oh, I'm sorry,
but our delivery truck is on its last trip

252
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:46,486
and won't be back
until after 11:00.

253
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,197
How about
a messenger boy?

