And of the girl
I'm taking

1044
01:06:47,295 --> 01:06:53,341
To the Easter parade

1045
01:06:55,511 --> 01:06:56,970
Hello!

1046
01:06:59,265 --> 01:07:01,016
I didn't exactly
expect the welcome mat,

1047
01:07:01,100 --> 01:07:02,809
but I thought somebody
might say hello.

1048
01:07:03,352 --> 01:07:04,853
Hello.
Thanks.

1049
01:07:04,937 --> 01:07:07,606
What brings you here
on this bright and uninviting day?

1050
01:07:08,107 --> 01:07:10,901
I've discovered something,
my friends, about life.

1051
01:07:11,527 --> 01:07:12,778
Meaning what?

1052
01:07:12,862 --> 01:07:15,405
Well, I don't want success,

1053
01:07:15,531 --> 01:07:19,117
I want the true happiness
you people have found here at the inn.

1054
01:07:19,202 --> 01:07:20,786
You're not gonna
stay in the inn?

1055
01:07:20,870 --> 01:07:22,996
Not just stay,
I want to be part of your shows,

1056
01:07:23,080 --> 01:07:24,623
help you in your work,

1057
01:07:24,707 --> 01:07:26,374
share your
simple pleasures.

1058
01:07:27,126 --> 01:07:29,336
I asked you once
not to interfere, Ted.

1059
01:07:29,420 --> 01:07:32,547
Please believe me,
I am a tired, lonely and unhappy man.

1060
01:07:32,632 --> 01:07:36,301
But I could be happy here,
helping the two people I like the best.

1061
01:07:36,761 --> 01:07:37,803
Will you take me in?

1062
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:38,887
My motherly intuition

1063
01:07:38,971 --> 01:07:40,806
tells me to
throw him out.

1064
01:07:40,890 --> 01:07:43,225
Well, at least give him
the benefit of the doubt.

1065
01:07:43,309 --> 01:07:45,185
I've given him
plenty of doubt.

1066
01:07:45,269 --> 01:07:48,522
Are you kidding
with that "sharing life's simple pleasures"?

1067
01:07:49,649 --> 01:07:50,941
May I go inside
with you?

1068
01:07:51,025 --> 01:07:52,234
Why, of course.

1069
01:07:52,902 --> 01:07:54,945
My... My trunks will
arrive this afternoon.

1070
01:07:55,029 --> 01:07:57,072
What do I do?
Move in the broom closet?

1071
01:07:57,156 --> 01:07:59,699
Jim, that's no way
to talk to a man who's here to help you.

1072
01:07:59,784 --> 01:08:01,409
The world
doesn't change.

1073
01:08:01,494 --> 01:08:04,204
A gentle smile
often breeds a kick in the pants.

1074
01:08:04,288 --> 01:08:07,082
But for your sake,
Linda, I'll be big.

1075
01:08:19,720 --> 01:08:21,471
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1076
01:08:27,186 --> 01:08:28,937
I'll give you a tip
about these things, Gus.

1077
01:08:29,021 --> 01:08:30,981
They'll go up and back,
but not sideways.

1078
01:08:31,065 --> 01:08:33,024
Yeah, well,
I keep forgetting

1079
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:35,110
this blind thing can't
see where it's going.

1080
01:08:35,194 --> 01:08:38,822
Yeah, well, unload
the rest of this stuff in the back, huh?

1081
01:08:38,906 --> 01:08:40,073
(ENGINE STARTS)

1082
01:08:40,867 --> 01:08:42,492
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1083
01:08:45,955 --> 01:08:48,665
TED: Hey! What did you do,
get up before breakfast?

1084
01:08:48,749 --> 01:08:50,375
Why, every morning.
I trust you slept well.

1085
01:08:50,459 --> 01:08:51,668
When I found out
how late you got in,

1086
01:08:51,752 --> 01:08:53,587
I told Mamie to
let you sleep.

1087
01:08:53,671 --> 01:08:55,589
(LAUGHS) Life on a farm!
Can't beat it, huh?

1088
01:08:55,673 --> 01:08:57,048
Jim, you've made me
very happy!

1089
01:08:57,133 --> 01:08:58,300
That's fine.

1090
01:08:58,384 --> 01:09:00,218
Now, how about
you making me happy?

1091
01:09:00,303 --> 01:09:02,387
You sound like a landlord
with eviction papers.

1092
01:09:02,471 --> 01:09:04,431
Oh. This is good news,
Lila's back in New York.

1093
01:09:04,515 --> 01:09:06,474
I got a letter
from her yesterday.

1094
01:09:06,559 --> 01:09:07,934
What happened to
her millionaire?

1095
01:09:08,019 --> 01:09:09,352
Slight mistake there.

1096
01:09:09,478 --> 01:09:12,230
He didn't own millions,
he owed them. (CHUCKLES)

1097
01:09:12,315 --> 01:09:16,026
Poor girl, always straying
to greener pastures and finding spinach.

1098
01:09:16,444 --> 01:09:17,569
Say, she was
wondering if you'd

1099
01:09:17,653 --> 01:09:19,613
be interested in
taking her back as a partner.

1100
01:09:19,697 --> 01:09:21,072
I think it'd be
a great idea.

1101
01:09:21,157 --> 01:09:22,490
Naturally, you would.

1102
01:09:22,950 --> 01:09:25,035
But I like it here
with you and Linda.

1103
01:09:25,119 --> 01:09:27,120
Yes, and we love
having you, too.

1104
01:09:28,581 --> 01:09:30,457
Uh, when are
you leaving?

1105
01:09:43,596 --> 01:09:45,597
Why didn't you
say something? You look so silly.

1106
01:09:45,681 --> 01:09:47,474
Where's Jim?
Inside.

1107
01:09:47,558 --> 01:09:49,935
Good. I've fixed it.
Here's the news

1108
01:09:50,019 --> 01:09:52,103
in one luscious word:
Hollywood!

1109
01:09:52,188 --> 01:09:54,898
Now, I told you,
I'm not leaving here until Linda goes with me.

1110
01:09:54,982 --> 01:09:57,275
But this is the setup
you needed to get her away from Jim.

1111
01:09:57,360 --> 01:09:58,985
Now, there are going
to be two Hollywood men here tonight

1112
01:09:59,070 --> 01:10:00,111
to see the show.

1113
01:10:00,196 --> 01:10:01,446
One's an important
director.

1114
01:10:01,530 --> 01:10:03,782
If they like your dancing,
you and Linda

1115
01:10:03,866 --> 01:10:06,242
will be on a westbound
train tomorrow.

1116
01:10:06,327 --> 01:10:08,536
We better find out
if Linda's interested. Ooh.

1117
01:10:08,621 --> 01:10:11,122
We let her know
when there's a contract staring her in the face.

1118
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:13,208
Look...
Now I know you're in love with the girl

1119
01:10:13,292 --> 01:10:15,001
but forget her until
we get her away from here.

1120
01:10:15,086 --> 01:10:16,795
This is no time
to be honest.

1121
01:10:16,879 --> 01:10:17,963
TED: Well,
what should I do?

1122
01:10:18,047 --> 01:10:20,173
All we have to do
is to convince Jim

1123
01:10:20,257 --> 01:10:22,801
that he'd be a heel
if he stood in the way of a chance like this.

1124
01:10:22,885 --> 01:10:25,387
Oh, that'll be easy,
like peeling a turtle.

1125
01:10:34,855 --> 01:10:36,189
Mamie says
these go up here!

1126
01:10:36,273 --> 01:10:38,525
Yes, set them right down.

1127
01:10:40,861 --> 01:10:44,280
Say, Gus, how would
you like to earn a slow $10?

1128
01:10:44,365 --> 01:10:47,158
Well, I don't care
how slow, but sure.

1129
01:10:47,243 --> 01:10:49,244
(CHUCKLES)
It's sure, all right, here's the wrinkle,

1130
01:10:49,328 --> 01:10:50,996
I want you to go
down to the station

1131
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:53,206
pick up a party and
start for Holiday Inn

1132
01:10:53,290 --> 01:10:55,291
but never get here.
Could you handle that?

1133
01:10:55,376 --> 01:10:56,668
Wouldn't be surprised!

1134
01:10:56,752 --> 01:10:59,295
Hello, long distance.

1135
01:10:59,380 --> 01:11:01,423
That's what I want you
to do with Linda Mason.

1136
01:11:01,507 --> 01:11:03,800
Miss Mason?
Our friend?

1137
01:11:03,884 --> 01:11:06,177
You're not supposed
to understand it, Gus.

1138
01:11:06,262 --> 01:11:10,015
For that kind of money
you ought to be able to go by way of Medicine Hat.

1139
01:11:10,099 --> 01:11:12,225
Hello, yeah.
Just a minute.

1140
01:11:15,229 --> 01:11:18,398
Long distance,
I want to get Parkway Hotel,

1141
01:11:18,482 --> 01:11:20,984
New York City,
Miss Lila Dixon.

1142
01:11:24,780 --> 01:11:26,448
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1143
01:11:44,467 --> 01:11:46,342
Didn't Linda say
she'd be here for final rehearsal?

1144
01:11:46,427 --> 01:11:49,846
Oh, relax,
our audiences aren't professional critics.

1145
01:12:04,236 --> 01:12:05,570
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1146
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:07,822
Gus, you made
a wrong turn.

1147
01:12:07,907 --> 01:12:09,115
Shortcut.

1148
01:12:13,496 --> 01:12:14,621
Gus!

1149
01:12:14,705 --> 01:12:16,122
Shortcut,
another shortcut.

1150
01:12:34,266 --> 01:12:36,518
How could you possibly
expect to drive through this?

1151
01:12:36,602 --> 01:12:38,937
Well, I never
had no trouble with a horse.

1152
01:12:42,399 --> 01:12:43,858
Oh, you'd better
carry me to shore,

1153
01:12:43,943 --> 01:12:45,610
and I'll walk
back to the highway.

1154
01:12:45,694 --> 01:12:48,822
Well, I think
you'd be better off waiting right here.

1155
01:12:48,906 --> 01:12:51,491
Gus, will you please
do as I say?

1156
01:12:52,743 --> 01:12:54,285
Oh, all right.

1157
01:13:00,543 --> 01:13:02,127
The other way.
Huh?

1158
01:13:02,211 --> 01:13:05,797
Turn around.
Gus, turn around!

1159
01:13:06,674 --> 01:13:07,715
Oh!

1160
01:13:10,261 --> 01:13:11,803
Gus!

1161
01:13:15,057 --> 01:13:16,808
My hat!
You pushed me.

1162
01:13:16,892 --> 01:13:18,059
Get my hat!

1163
01:13:24,024 --> 01:13:26,317
I swear the show will
start any minute now.

1164
01:13:26,402 --> 01:13:28,611
You said that
an hour ago.

1165
01:13:28,696 --> 01:13:32,198
Yeah, but this time
I'm sincere. Excuse me.

1166
01:13:38,497 --> 01:13:40,206
(LET'S SAY IT WITH
FIRECRACKERS PLAYING)

1167
01:13:56,015 --> 01:13:57,348
Who started the show?

1168
01:13:57,433 --> 01:13:58,683
I did. You're on.

1169
01:13:58,767 --> 01:14:00,018
But what about
Ted's partner?

1170
01:14:00,102 --> 01:14:02,729
You've kept this crowd
waiting long enough, he can go on without her.

1171
01:14:02,813 --> 01:14:04,564
Have you gone nuts?
I've rehearsed a double dance.

1172
01:14:04,690 --> 01:14:09,736
(SINGING)
Let's say it with firecrackers and banners held high

1173
01:14:09,820 --> 01:14:14,908
Let's have
a real old-fashioned noisy Fourth of July

1174
01:14:15,409 --> 01:14:17,869
Let's say it
with firecrackers

1175
01:14:17,953 --> 01:14:20,121
They'll jump at up North

1176
01:14:20,206 --> 01:14:25,376
Let's have the kind
we used to call a glorious Fourth

1177
01:14:25,586 --> 01:14:28,087
Let's salute
our native land

1178
01:14:28,172 --> 01:14:30,048
Roman candles
in each hand

1179
01:14:30,591 --> 01:14:33,176
While a Yankee Doodle band

1180
01:14:33,260 --> 01:14:35,762
Gets hotter
than a firecracker

1181
01:14:35,846 --> 01:14:38,389
Don't need
any long speeches

1182
01:14:38,474 --> 01:14:40,391
Or shouts of "Hooray!"

1183
01:14:40,726 --> 01:14:45,521
No words can say as much
as firecrackers can say

1184
01:14:50,986 --> 01:14:56,241
Freedom! Freedom!

1185
01:14:56,325 --> 01:15:00,828
Here comes the Freedom Man

1186
01:15:00,913 --> 01:15:03,581
On this day
of independence

1187
01:15:03,666 --> 01:15:06,042
On this Independence Day

1188
01:15:06,126 --> 01:15:11,714
Listen to
an American troubadour from the U.S.A.

1189
01:15:11,799 --> 01:15:16,761
I'm singing a song
of freedom

1190
01:15:16,845 --> 01:15:22,392
For all people who
cry out to be free

1191
01:15:23,435 --> 01:15:26,354
Free to sail
the seven seas

1192
01:15:26,438 --> 01:15:29,232
Free to worship
as we please

1193
01:15:29,316 --> 01:15:31,359
If the birds
up in the trees

1194
01:15:31,443 --> 01:15:32,610
Can be free

1195
01:15:32,695 --> 01:15:34,988
Why can't we?

1196
01:15:35,072 --> 01:15:40,326
I'm bringing a song
of freedom

1197
01:15:40,411 --> 01:15:46,332
To all people
wherever they may be

1198
01:15:46,417 --> 01:15:49,377
Free to speak
and free to hear

1199
01:15:49,461 --> 01:15:52,338
Free from want
and free from fear

1200
01:15:52,423 --> 01:15:54,549
Sons of freedom
far and near

1201
01:15:54,633 --> 01:15:55,758
Who agree

1202
01:15:55,843 --> 01:15:57,635
Sing with me

1203
01:15:57,803 --> 01:16:03,641
That all God's people
shall be free

1204
