1221
01:17:09,958 --> 01:17:10,917
Will you give me a lift?

1222
01:17:11,001 --> 01:17:12,502
Sure, hop in.

1223
01:17:19,927 --> 01:17:22,428
Aren't you Ted Hanover's
former dancing partner?

1224
01:17:23,680 --> 01:17:27,266
Yes, although
I wouldn't exactly say former.

1225
01:17:27,643 --> 01:17:29,394
I'm dancing with him
at the inn tonight.

1226
01:17:30,604 --> 01:17:34,273
But I... Doesn't he
have a new partner?

1227
01:17:34,358 --> 01:17:36,150
Oh, she won't be
there tonight.

1228
01:17:36,235 --> 01:17:37,985
I didn't know that!

1229
01:17:39,113 --> 01:17:40,321
I work at the inn.

1230
01:17:40,406 --> 01:17:41,531
Oh?

1231
01:17:42,783 --> 01:17:44,242
Waitress?

1232
01:17:44,326 --> 01:17:45,701
Yes.

1233
01:17:46,954 --> 01:17:50,706
I know your boss,
Jim Hardy, quite well. Quite well.

1234
01:17:51,959 --> 01:17:54,961
Then he's responsible for
your rejoining Mr. Hanover.

1235
01:17:55,045 --> 01:17:56,295
Uh-huh.

1236
01:17:56,463 --> 01:17:58,548
By the way, if I were you,
I'd look my prettiest tonight

1237
01:17:58,632 --> 01:17:59,841
when I'm waiting on tables.

1238
01:17:59,925 --> 01:18:01,592
Jim says there will
be a couple of men from Hollywood

1239
01:18:01,677 --> 01:18:03,177
to consider Ted and me
for pictures.

1240
01:18:04,513 --> 01:18:06,264
And Mr. Hanover's
other partner

1241
01:18:06,348 --> 01:18:08,558
will be missing this chance
to go to Hollywood.

1242
01:18:08,642 --> 01:18:10,601
Yes, although she can't
be very talented

1243
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:12,645
or they wouldn't be
working at the inn.

1244
01:18:12,729 --> 01:18:15,106
Ted and I played
only the best places.

1245
01:18:17,943 --> 01:18:20,236
Listen, you're late
for the show already,

1246
01:18:20,320 --> 01:18:21,612
if you'd care
to let me drive

1247
01:18:21,697 --> 01:18:24,657
I know a shortcut
that'll get us there 15 minutes sooner.

1248
01:18:30,581 --> 01:18:32,081
There's a farmhouse
near here

1249
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:33,583
and I'll have us towed out
in a couple of minutes.

1250
01:18:33,667 --> 01:18:34,917
Oh, for the love
of mud, hurry!

1251
01:18:35,002 --> 01:18:36,377
Wait right here!

1252
01:18:36,462 --> 01:18:37,837
What else can I do?

1253
01:18:42,885 --> 01:18:44,135
(ALL APPLAUDING)

1254
01:18:44,219 --> 01:18:45,678
(BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYING)

1255
01:18:45,762 --> 01:18:47,722
You're on now.
But Linda isn't here yet.

1256
01:18:47,806 --> 01:18:49,015
You've got to
save the pieces,

1257
01:18:49,099 --> 01:18:50,141
keep those men
interested now

1258
01:18:50,225 --> 01:18:51,309
and do a number
with Linda later.

1259
01:18:51,393 --> 01:18:52,435
What can I do?

1260
01:18:52,519 --> 01:18:54,395
Well, fake something.

1261
01:18:54,480 --> 01:18:56,355
Fake something, okay.

1262
01:19:02,696 --> 01:19:03,946
There's your cue.

1263
01:19:04,198 --> 01:19:06,282
Don't fail me,
keep them flying.

1264
01:19:06,366 --> 01:19:07,658
I'll keep them flying.

1265
01:19:29,264 --> 01:19:30,723
(FIRECRACKER BURSTS)

1266
01:21:59,081 --> 01:22:00,539
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1267
01:22:17,265 --> 01:22:20,518
Linda!
What happened to you?

1268
01:22:20,602 --> 01:22:21,894
A bad job of sabotage.

1269
01:22:24,481 --> 01:22:25,648
Excuse me!

1270
01:22:29,194 --> 01:22:30,903
Well, Jim,
you deliberately kept me

1271
01:22:30,987 --> 01:22:32,905
from working at
the inn tonight, didn't you?

1272
01:22:32,989 --> 01:22:34,573
Yeah.
You knew there would be men here

1273
01:22:34,658 --> 01:22:37,284
from Hollywood
who might offer me a chance in pictures.

1274
01:22:37,411 --> 01:22:39,704
You've decided
I shouldn't have that opportunity.

1275
01:22:39,788 --> 01:22:42,164
Not even
the opportunity to refuse.

1276
01:22:42,249 --> 01:22:43,791
I was afraid
the offer might

1277
01:22:43,875 --> 01:22:45,918
be too important
for you to turn down.

1278
01:22:46,002 --> 01:22:48,379
The point is
you don't trust me to make my own decisions

1279
01:22:48,463 --> 01:22:51,298
because they might
interfere with your own selfish plans.

1280
01:22:51,425 --> 01:22:54,427
I've had about
enough of that, Jim.

1281
01:22:54,511 --> 01:22:56,429
Ted, Linda!

1282
01:22:56,513 --> 01:22:58,347
Mr. Parker,
Mr. Dunbar,

1283
01:22:58,432 --> 01:22:59,557
I want you to meet
the greatest dance team

1284
01:22:59,641 --> 01:23:01,434
in show business,
Hanover and Mason.

1285
01:23:01,518 --> 01:23:03,060
And the owner
Jim Hardy.

1286
01:23:03,145 --> 01:23:05,479
Glad to know you, Hardy.
Nice little place you've got here.

1287
01:23:05,564 --> 01:23:06,731
Gentlemen, even though
you haven't seen

1288
01:23:06,815 --> 01:23:08,524
Miss Mason dance,
I can assure you...

1289
01:23:08,608 --> 01:23:10,151
Hardy, Hollywood
is always interested

1290
01:23:10,235 --> 01:23:12,361
in new ideas
and we think this is a honey.

1291
01:23:12,446 --> 01:23:14,864
Frankly, we'd like to
do a picture based on the Holiday Inn.

1292
01:23:14,948 --> 01:23:17,825
The idea behind it,
how it works, the special holiday songs.

1293
01:23:17,909 --> 01:23:20,161
Of course, it's purely
a speculative thing, far from foolproof

1294
01:23:20,245 --> 01:23:21,954
and we can't afford
to pay too much.

1295
01:23:22,038 --> 01:23:23,664
You don't have to
start talking it down

1296
01:23:23,749 --> 01:23:25,750
because the idea
is not for sale.

1297
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:27,334
Well, maybe I haven't
explained enough.

1298
01:23:27,419 --> 01:23:30,713
We expect to use Mr. Hanover
and his partner in the picture.

1299
01:23:30,797 --> 01:23:32,548
Well, I don't know
how the others feel

1300
01:23:32,632 --> 01:23:35,217
but I'd like to
keep this little setup just the way it is.

1301
01:23:35,343 --> 01:23:36,594
Jim, would you be
decent just once

1302
01:23:36,678 --> 01:23:38,637
and let somebody else
around here have a chance?

1303
01:23:38,722 --> 01:23:40,347
Wait a minute, Danny,
after all, the place belongs to him

1304
01:23:40,432 --> 01:23:42,224
he can do as he wants.

1305
01:23:42,309 --> 01:23:44,810
I guess it was just
too good to last, huh?

1306
01:23:44,895 --> 01:23:46,771
A simple little layout,
where we could do our best

1307
01:23:46,855 --> 01:23:49,690
at the work we know
without having any illusions of glory.

1308
01:23:51,151 --> 01:23:54,487
I can see now that
I'm the only one who could be happy here.

1309
01:23:54,571 --> 01:23:56,322
Go ahead,
take the idea, take the music,

1310
01:23:56,406 --> 01:23:58,115
take Linda,
take the whole darn thing.

1311
01:23:58,200 --> 01:23:59,450
But what about you?
We'll need you

1312
01:23:59,534 --> 01:24:01,327
in Hollywood to write
the rest of the music.

1313
01:24:01,411 --> 01:24:03,287
Oh, no,
I work right here.

1314
01:24:03,371 --> 01:24:05,372
I'll send you the music
when it's written.

1315
01:24:05,457 --> 01:24:07,875
And don't bother
me before, huh?

1316
01:24:10,295 --> 01:24:12,463
Guess maybe I was
a little selfish, huh?

1317
01:24:12,547 --> 01:24:14,799
Is that the deal you wanted
or should I have thrown in my shirt?

1318
01:24:18,678 --> 01:24:20,262
Chummy sort of a fellow,
isn't he?

1319
01:24:20,347 --> 01:24:23,766
Listen, Linda,
if you really want to stay here...

1320
01:24:23,850 --> 01:24:27,186
Don't talk that way.
This is the chance you wanted, isn't it?

1321
01:24:27,270 --> 01:24:30,523
Of course.
Boy, are we happy!

1322
01:27:08,807 --> 01:27:10,933
Happy Thanksgiving,
Mr. Jim.

1323
01:27:11,017 --> 01:27:13,644
Same to you, Mamie.
And staff.

1324
01:27:13,770 --> 01:27:16,271
Didn't I tell you children
to stay in the kitchen?

1325
01:27:16,356 --> 01:27:19,274
Those wings ain't
going to fly away. Now shoo!

1326
01:27:21,444 --> 01:27:23,362
Everything's
ready and hot, Mr. Jim.

1327
01:27:23,446 --> 01:27:24,738
Thank you, Mamie.

1328
01:27:42,090 --> 01:27:44,216
(I'VE GOT PLENTY
TO BE THANKFUL FOR PLAYING)

1329
01:27:45,135 --> 01:27:48,971
I've got plenty
to be thankful for

1330
01:27:49,222 --> 01:27:50,723
Are you kidding?

1331
01:27:50,807 --> 01:27:54,226
I haven't got
a great big yacht

1332
01:27:54,310 --> 01:27:57,354
To sail from
shore to shore

1333
01:27:57,439 --> 01:28:01,483
Still I've got plenty
to be thankful for

1334
01:28:01,568 --> 01:28:03,318
You're loaded, Dan.

1335
01:28:03,403 --> 01:28:07,531
I've got plenty
to be thankful for

1336
01:28:07,615 --> 01:28:08,782
Like what?

1337
01:28:08,950 --> 01:28:10,576
No private car

1338
01:28:10,660 --> 01:28:11,869
No caviar

1339
01:28:11,953 --> 01:28:14,955
No carpet on my floor

1340
01:28:15,707 --> 01:28:19,793
Still I've got plenty
to be thankful for

1341
01:28:19,878 --> 01:28:21,295
You know you're
better off than I am.

1342
01:28:21,379 --> 01:28:23,505
I've got eyes
to see with

1343
01:28:23,590 --> 01:28:24,715
You need glasses.

1344
01:28:24,799 --> 01:28:26,508
Ears to hear with

1345
01:28:26,593 --> 01:28:27,676
Or fly with.

1346
01:28:27,761 --> 01:28:29,053
Arms to hug with

1347
01:28:29,137 --> 01:28:30,637
Lips to kiss with

1348
01:28:30,722 --> 01:28:32,681
Someone to adore

1349
01:28:32,766 --> 01:28:33,849
You're a little flat, too.

1350
01:28:33,933 --> 01:28:39,104
How could
anybody ask for more?

1351
01:28:39,189 --> 01:28:42,107
My needs are small
I buy them all

1352
01:28:42,192 --> 01:28:45,486
At the five and ten cent store

1353
01:28:45,570 --> 01:28:46,695
Sing it!

1354
01:28:46,780 --> 01:28:47,863
Sing it pretty.

1355
01:28:47,947 --> 01:28:50,199
Oh, I've got plenty
to be thankful for

1356
01:28:55,330 --> 01:28:57,081
Why, you ain't
ate a bite.

1357
01:28:58,500 --> 01:29:00,000
I'm pouting, Mamie.

1358
01:29:00,085 --> 01:29:01,126
Who is this?

1359
01:29:01,211 --> 01:29:02,586
That's Mr. Jones.

1360
01:29:02,670 --> 01:29:05,714
Jonesey! I'm sorry,
I knew him too well.

1361
01:29:05,799 --> 01:29:07,508
But you got to eat.

1362
01:29:07,592 --> 01:29:11,261
The trouble ain't
with that turkey, Mr. Jim, it's you!

1363
01:29:11,346 --> 01:29:14,139
I feel all right.
I'm riding high, Mamie.

1364
01:29:14,224 --> 01:29:16,433
Well, why you close
the inn and sit around

1365
01:29:16,518 --> 01:29:18,477
like a jellyfish
with the misery?

1366
01:29:18,561 --> 01:29:20,646
'Cause a slicker
stole your gal

1367
01:29:20,730 --> 01:29:23,315
and you ain't got
fight enough to get her back.

1368
01:29:25,485 --> 01:29:26,777
Excuse me, Mr. Jim.

1369
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:28,612
I tried to
keep her here!

1370
01:29:28,696 --> 01:29:30,572
What kind of keeping
is that?

1371
01:29:30,657 --> 01:29:33,700
Nothing but tricks.
If you went to Hollywood

1372
01:29:33,785 --> 01:29:35,953
and told Miss Linda
how much you loves her,

1373
01:29:36,037 --> 01:29:38,288
and misses her,
and told her that

1374
01:29:38,373 --> 01:29:40,874
the way a lady
likes to hear it told,

1375
01:29:40,959 --> 01:29:46,505
I'll bet you she'd be
the quickest ex-movie star that ever exed.

1376
01:29:46,589 --> 01:29:48,257
You're crazy, Mamie

1377
01:29:48,341 --> 01:29:52,719
I'm crazy?
I knows Miss Linda.

1378
01:29:52,804 --> 01:29:56,181
I knows her like
I knows my own kids.

1379
01:29:56,266 --> 01:29:59,643
Why, she ain't
the fancy type no more than you are.

1380
01:29:59,727 --> 01:30:03,355
What she wants is
what you got right here.

1381
01:30:03,439 --> 01:30:07,442
But women has to
have them things told to them the right way.

1382
01:30:07,527 --> 01:30:10,737
You could melt her heart
right down to butter,

1383
01:30:10,822 --> 01:30:14,032
if you'd only
turn on the heat.

1384
01:30:14,117 --> 01:30:16,994
Mamie, you don't try
to take a fellow's gal

1385
01:30:17,078 --> 01:30:19,246
away from him after
he's bought the ring.

1386
01:30:21,666 --> 01:30:23,167
Or as I recall, do you?

1387
01:30:23,251 --> 01:30:25,419
Now you're talking!

1388
01:30:25,503 --> 01:30:28,380
Oh, sure, women has to be
told things the right way.

1389
01:30:28,464 --> 01:30:29,631
MAMIE: Yes, sir!

1390
01:30:42,687 --> 01:30:46,565
At last, the night
I've been dreaming about actually here.

1391
01:30:46,649 --> 01:30:48,066
This is still
my wedding, you know.

1392
01:30:48,151 --> 01:30:49,526
You make me feel
like a kibitzer.

1393
01:30:49,611 --> 01:30:52,529
Now don't misunderstand me,
I'm happy because this marriage means

1394
01:30:52,614 --> 01:30:55,115
that we can all
settle down and stop worrying.

1395
01:30:55,200 --> 01:30:57,701
I wish
I had your confidence without your viewpoint.

1396
01:30:57,785 --> 01:30:59,620
My fingers are crossed
until Linda and I

1397
01:30:59,704 --> 01:31:01,205
are on that plane
bound for Yuma.

1398
01:31:01,289 --> 01:31:02,873
Now what's worrying you?

1399
01:31:02,957 --> 01:31:05,083
I don't know, except
I've been this close to marriage before

1400
01:31:05,168 --> 01:31:06,376
only to wake up
next morning

1401
01:31:06,461 --> 01:31:08,462
and find myself with
no bride and a hangover.

1402
01:31:08,546 --> 01:31:10,923
Look, the girl said yes,
the picture finishes tonight,

1403
01:31:11,049 --> 01:31:13,050
there's a judge
waiting in Yuma. (KNOCKING ON DOOR)

1404
01:31:13,134 --> 01:31:14,176
Come in!

1405
01:31:14,260 --> 01:31:15,636
Everything is
all set and ready.

1406
01:31:15,720 --> 01:31:18,639
What could
possibly happen to...

1407
01:31:18,723 --> 01:31:20,390
Hi, fellows!

1408
01:31:23,436 --> 01:31:26,188
Jim, what brought
you here?

1409
01:31:26,272 --> 01:31:27,940
Train.
Chug chug chug chug.

1410
01:31:28,733 --> 01:31:30,442
The wedding,
when is it?

1411
01:31:30,526 --> 01:31:32,694
Wedding?
Yeah.

1412
01:31:32,779 --> 01:31:34,947
Well, we hadn't
set any exact time.

1413
01:31:35,031 --> 01:31:36,406
Have you seen Linda?

1414
01:31:36,491 --> 01:31:38,867
No, no, not yet.
But, say, I saw your director,

1415
01:31:38,952 --> 01:31:40,994
he told me
he was shooting the finale tonight,

1416
01:31:41,079 --> 01:31:42,704
thought I'd like to see
how you make pictures.

1417
01:31:43,665 --> 01:31:46,083
He wouldn't...
You wouldn't like what they're doing tonight.

1418
01:31:46,167 --> 01:31:47,251
Why not?

1419
01:31:47,335 --> 01:31:48,835
Oh, no, that's dull,
technical stuff.

1420
01:31:48,920 --> 01:31:51,129
Well, I'm a dull,
technical sort of a fellow.

1421
01:31:51,214 --> 01:31:53,715
Perhaps if you'd wait
and see Linda tomorrow.

1422
01:31:53,800 --> 01:31:56,718
Oh, no, I want to
see the finish.

1423
01:31:56,803 --> 01:32:00,222
The success of you
and Linda means a lot to me, pal.

1424
01:32:00,306 --> 01:32:02,557
Say, why don't
you be yourself. What are you up to?

1425
01:32:04,227 --> 01:32:07,479
Well, I'm a son of a gun.
This is a beautiful hunk of welcome

1426
01:32:07,563 --> 01:32:08,981
for a guy who
comes coast to coast

1427
01:32:09,065 --> 01:32:11,733
just to wish you
a merry Christmas and a happy wedding.

1428
01:32:12,068 --> 01:32:13,277
(CHUCKLES)

1429
01:32:13,361 --> 01:32:14,820
You remember how
I suspected you

1430
01:32:14,904 --> 01:32:16,989
when you came to
live at the inn on Easter morning?

1431
01:32:17,865 --> 01:32:19,032
Silly, wasn't it?

1432
01:32:19,117 --> 01:32:20,242
Now I know he's
up to something.

1433
01:32:20,326 --> 01:32:21,660
Oh, wait a minute now
let's not be unfair.

1434
01:32:21,744 --> 01:32:22,744
No?

1435
01:32:22,829 --> 01:32:25,330
No, we're treating Jim
like a poor country cousin.

1436
01:32:25,415 --> 01:32:26,790
He doesn't mean
any harm! No!

1437
01:32:26,874 --> 01:32:28,625
No, he just wants
to see Linda.

1438
01:32:28,710 --> 01:32:31,044
So let's show him Linda.

1439
01:32:31,129 --> 01:32:32,879
Goodwill on earth
toward men.

1440
01:32:33,006 --> 01:32:35,090
This... Where we going?
What's this?

1441
01:32:36,926 --> 01:32:39,219
Hey, Ted! What is this?

1442
01:32:39,304 --> 01:32:40,929
TED: I was afraid
you'd gone crazy.

1443
01:32:41,014 --> 01:32:44,683
DANNY: I'll keep him in here
till you get Linda on that plane.

1444
01:32:46,728 --> 01:32:48,061
TED: I better hurry
and get my clothes on.

1445
01:32:48,146 --> 01:32:49,563
DANNY: Yeah,
in the meantime I'll go down to the set

1446
01:32:49,647 --> 01:32:51,023
and see how near
ready they are.

1447
01:32:51,107 --> 01:32:52,816
TED: Wait a minute,
my clothes are in there.

1448
01:32:52,900 --> 01:32:54,526
Merry Christmas!

1449
01:32:54,610 --> 01:32:56,445
Jim, pal! Wait!

1450
01:32:56,529 --> 01:32:58,322
Stop!
We were only fooling!

1451
01:32:59,949 --> 01:33:02,909
Only you could think
of a thing like that.

1452
01:33:09,125 --> 01:33:11,001
Who you calling?

1453
01:33:11,085 --> 01:33:13,545
Nobody,
the operator's gone.

1454
01:33:45,244 --> 01:33:47,871
Take it easy.
Don't break your neck.

1455
01:33:54,379 --> 01:33:56,671
It's one of the most
authentic reproduction jobs we've ever done.

1456
01:33:56,756 --> 01:33:57,881
Is it?

1457
01:33:57,965 --> 01:33:59,299
And all worked out
from those photographs

1458
01:33:59,384 --> 01:34:00,884
we took of your place
in Connecticut.

1459
01:34:00,968 --> 01:34:02,469
Uh-huh.

1460
01:34:04,180 --> 01:34:06,973
Well, Mamie and the kids
ought to see this. They'd never believe it!

1461
01:34:07,850 --> 01:34:09,309
Anything wrong?

1462
01:34:09,394 --> 01:34:12,020
Well, that Christmas tree's
a little out of place.

1463
01:34:12,105 --> 01:34:15,649
I'd guess nobody
would notice that but me or Linda.

1464
01:34:15,733 --> 01:34:17,484
We're going to
start rolling in a couple of minutes.

1465
01:34:17,568 --> 01:34:18,902
Come along with me
where you can see everything.

1466
01:34:18,986 --> 01:34:20,445
No, I'll just sort of
stay in the background.

1467
01:34:20,530 --> 01:34:21,947
I don't want to
get in your way.

1468
01:34:22,031 --> 01:34:23,657
Well, suit yourself.
I'll see you later.

1469
01:34:23,741 --> 01:34:25,033
Right.

1470
01:34:44,887 --> 01:34:46,263
All right, darling,
we're going to follow you

1471
01:34:46,347 --> 01:34:48,098
on the boom from
here inside the inn.

1472
01:34:48,182 --> 01:34:50,684
And when you get
in the other set, do your song.

1473
01:34:50,810 --> 01:34:52,602
Let's see, I think
you have the mood,

1474
01:34:52,687 --> 01:34:54,479
your Hollywood
success was empty,

1475
01:34:54,564 --> 01:34:57,732
you've lost
the one man you love. You know, the usual hope.

1476
01:34:58,818 --> 01:35:01,528
Just make me cry
and you can get to that wedding.

1477
01:35:01,612 --> 01:35:02,863
All ready for rehearsal!

1478
01:35:02,947 --> 01:35:04,906
Please! Let's shoot it.

1479
01:35:04,991 --> 01:35:07,284
Okay, it's a take!

1480
01:35:10,872 --> 01:35:14,249
All right, everybody,
quiet on the stage, it's a take.

1481
01:35:14,375 --> 01:35:17,252
(ALARM RINGING)
Close them up. Come on, over there,

1482
01:35:17,336 --> 01:35:19,588
quiet down,
let's get settled, everybody.

1483
01:35:22,842 --> 01:35:26,052
Come on, everybody,
let's get settled now. This is the picture.

1484
01:35:26,262 --> 01:35:27,262
(INAUDIBLE)

1485
01:35:28,181 --> 01:35:29,264
Hit the snow!

1486
01:35:31,893 --> 01:35:33,185
All right, roll 'em!

1487
01:35:35,688 --> 01:35:36,688
(BELL RINGS)

1488
01:35:39,692 --> 01:35:41,651
Sorry, Mr. Hanover,
but when the red light's on

1489
01:35:41,736 --> 01:35:43,778
you couldn't get in
even if you owned the studio.

1490
01:35:43,863 --> 01:35:45,155
Oh, but, pop,
this is important.

1491
01:35:45,239 --> 01:35:46,490
I know,
so is the light.

1492
01:35:46,574 --> 01:35:48,283
Hit the playback.
Music!

1493
01:35:49,911 --> 01:35:51,077
(SOFT ORCHESTRAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1494
01:35:52,705 --> 01:35:54,331
All right, action!

1495
01:35:59,003 --> 01:36:01,087
(WHITE CHRISTMAS PLAYING)

1496
01:37:14,662 --> 01:37:21,376
(SINGING) I'm dreaming
of a white Christmas

1497
01:37:22,962 --> 01:37:27,424
Just like the ones
I used to know

1498
01:37:29,760 --> 01:37:34,139
Where the treetops glisten

1499
01:37:34,682 --> 01:37:38,893
And children listen

1500
01:37:38,978 --> 01:37:44,899
To hear sleigh bells
in the snow

1501
01:37:49,405 --> 01:37:50,530
(JIM WHISTLING TUNE)

1502
01:37:50,615 --> 01:37:53,199
...dreaming of a white

1503
01:37:54,660 --> 01:37:56,286
Christmas

1504
01:37:56,370 --> 01:37:57,370
(JIM HUMMING)

1505
01:37:57,455 --> 01:38:02,459
With every
Christmas card I write

1506
01:38:05,379 --> 01:38:11,259
May your days be
merry and bright

1507
01:38:14,680 --> 01:38:15,972
Jim!

1508
01:38:17,058 --> 01:38:18,141
Cut it! Cut it!

1509
01:38:18,684 --> 01:38:19,934
(BELL RINGS)
That's it!

1510
01:38:20,645 --> 01:38:22,187
All right, gentlemen!

1511
01:38:27,360 --> 01:38:29,653
How could
he get that far in five minutes?

1512
01:38:29,737 --> 01:38:31,863
The lady must
have been willing.

1513
01:38:31,947 --> 01:38:34,324
But the world
can't do this to us.

1514
01:38:34,909 --> 01:38:35,909
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

1515
01:38:45,920 --> 01:38:47,295
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1516
01:38:47,546 --> 01:38:49,089
(SWING MUSIC PLAYING)

1517
01:38:51,884 --> 01:38:54,302
(SINGING)
Here she comes down the street

1518
01:38:54,387 --> 01:38:56,638
I'll admit my defeat

1519
01:38:56,764 --> 01:38:59,432
I've won my hot toddy

1520
01:38:59,517 --> 01:39:01,601
Over my scarred body

1521
01:39:01,769 --> 01:39:08,066
I knew that
I'd win singing

1522
01:39:08,317 --> 01:39:11,695
But wait until
she gets a load of your dancing

1523
01:39:13,072 --> 01:39:18,660
We'll stay at
the inn singing

1524
01:39:19,453 --> 01:39:22,747
All by myself
I'll have to stick to my dancing

1525
01:39:26,252 --> 01:39:28,753
Oh, no, my friend,
I'm here to end

1526
01:39:28,838 --> 01:39:31,297
Your dancing
trouble and strife

1527
01:39:31,382 --> 01:39:34,050
This will be fun,
Miss Hit-and-Run

1528
01:39:34,135 --> 01:39:36,803
Has come back
into my life

1529
01:39:36,887 --> 01:39:38,722
We'll stay at the inn...

1530
01:39:38,806 --> 01:39:40,515
We'll have to begin...

1531
01:39:40,599 --> 01:39:41,766
Singing!

1532
01:39:41,851 --> 01:39:43,560
Dancing!

1533
01:39:52,361 --> 01:39:54,946
We've each other
to cling to

1534
01:39:55,030 --> 01:39:56,823
You'll be easy
to sing to

1535
01:39:57,032 --> 01:40:01,703
And you're easy
to dance with

1536
01:40:01,787 --> 01:40:07,542
So let the old year die
with a fond good-bye

1537
01:40:07,626 --> 01:40:12,505
And our hopes
as high as a kite

1538
01:40:14,216 --> 01:40:17,927
How can our love
go wrong

1539
01:40:18,012 --> 01:40:24,934
If we start
the new year right?

